reporter_caption.center: MIDWAY NATL. BANK OF ST. PAUL v. McGOUGH, 305 Minn. 503 (1975)

caption.center: MIDWAY NATIONAL BANK OF ST. PAUL v. MICHAEL J. McGOUGH AND ANOTHER.

opinion.syllabus: Unlawful detainer — appeal from judgment of restitution — issues without merit.
opinion.posture: Unlawful detainer proceeding in the municipal court of St. Paul, Ramsey County, initiated by Midway National Bank of St. Paul against Michael J McGough and Anne K. McGough. After adverse findings, Joseph P. Summers, Judge, defendants appealed from the judgment entered. Affirmed.
opinion.attorneys:
Michael J. McGough, pro se, for appellants.
Murnane, Murnane, Battis Conlin and Michael I. Fahey, for respondent.
opinion.panel: Considered and decided by the court without oral argument.
opinion.opinion_text:
Defendants appeal from a judgment of restitution in an unlawful detainer proceeding brought by plaintiff to regain possession of premises from defendants after cancellation of a contract for deed. The main issues raised by defendants relate to the propriety of service of the notice of cancellation of the contract for deed and of the summons and complaint in the unlawful detainer action. We have carefully considered these and other issues raised by defendants and find them to be without merit.
Affirmed.Page 504
